RASPBERRYPI PICO W wiring:

Step 1: Connection diagram (Wiring)

Before we write the code, we need to combine it all. We will use the I2C bus for the OLED display and one digital pin for the LED matrix.

Power Supply (Common):

Display OLED and matrix WS2812B need power.

Pico W Pin 36 (3V3 OUT) -> VCC display OLED.

Pico W Pin 40 (VBUS) -> VCC (5V) matrix LED. (Matrix WS2812B Works on 5V. Pin VBUS hale 5V from USB Cable. The control signal from Pico will have 3.3V).

Pico W Pin 38 (GND) -> GND display OLED and GND matrix LED. (All GND must be connected to each other).

Display OLED (I2C):

Pico W Pin 6 (GP4) -> SDA on OLED.

Pico W Pin 7 (GP5) -> SCL on OLED.

Matrix LED WS2812B (Signal):

Pico W Pin 4 (GP2) -> DIN (Data IN) on matrix LED.

